{"id":"309588126_Proving_Craig_and_Lyndon_Interpolation_Using_Labelled_Sequent_Calculi","abstract":"Interpolation is a fundamental logical property with applications\nin mathematics, computer science, and artificial intelligence. In\nthis paper, we develop a general method of translating a semantic description\nof modal logics via Kripke models into a constructive proof\nof the Lyndon interpolation property (LIP) via labelled sequents. Using\nthis method we demonstrate that all frame conditions representable as\nHorn formulas imply the LIP and that all 15 logics of the modal cube,\nas well as the infinite family of transitive Geach logics, enjoy the LIP.","authors":["Roman Kuznets"],"meta":["November 2016Lecture Notes in Computer Science 10021:320-335","DOI:10.1007/978-3-319-48758-8_21","Conference: JELIA 2016: Logics in Artificial IntelligenceAt: Larnaca, Cyprus","Project: Interpolation"],"references":["325068395_Uniform_interpolation_and_sequent_calculi_in_modal_logic","265439881_Interpolation_in_computing_science_The_semantics_of_modularization","220706010_Simulation_of_Two_Dimensions_in_Unimodal_Logics","326469827_Beth_Definability_in_Expressive_Description_Logics","321519307_Applied_Logic_Series","308735621_Interpolation_with_Decidable_Fixpoint_Logics","282857056_Interpolation_Method_for_Multicomponent_Sequent_Calculi","279217931_Geometrisation_of_First-Order_Logic","273354843_Craig_Interpolation_via_Hypersequents","271852212_Modal_interpolation_via_nested_sequents","266859257_Labelled_tree_sequents_tree_hypersequents_and_nested_Deep_sequents","266071964_Logic_and_Artificial_Intelligence","265880163_Multi-Dimensional_Modal_Logic","265817915_Proof_analysis_A_contribution_to_Hilbert's_last_problem","261157315_The_Logic_of_Exact_Covers_Completeness_and_Uniform_Interpolation","250602912_Absence_of_the_interpolation_property_in_the_consistent_normal_modal_extensions_of_the_dummett_logic","240057110_Interpolation_and_Definability_Modal_and_Intuitionistic_Logic","2279